# Fix Database Persistence and Add Image Upload Options

This plan addresses two main issues:
1. Centralized databases in AppHost losing data on restart
2. Providing an option to upload an image file instead of only providing a URL in Web forms

## Proposed Changes

### AppHost Configuration

#### [AppHost.cs](file:///c:/Users/Libert/Documents/Visual%20Studio%2018/Projets/GPOE26/GPOE26.AppHost/AppHost.cs)
- Add `.WithDataVolume()` immediately after `.AddPostgres("postgres")` to instruct Aspire to create a durable Docker volume for the PostgreSQL container, ensuring data persistence across application restarts.

---

### API Service (Backend)

#### [Program.cs](file:///c:/Users/Libert/Documents/Visual%20Studio%2018/Projets/GPOE26/GPOE26.ApiService/Program.cs)
- Add `app.UseStaticFiles()` to serve uploaded files.
- Create an endpoint `POST /api/upload` taking an `IFormFile`:
  - Validates the input
  - Saves the file inside `wwwroot/uploads/images`
  - Returns the URL of the saved file relative to the API service (e.g. `https://apiservice/uploads/images/filename.jpg` if requested, or just the relative path). We'll return the absolute URL `https://localhost:7192/...` or allow [ApiClient](file:///c:/Users/Libert/Documents/Visual%20Studio%2018/Projets/GPOE26/GPOE26.Web/Services/ApiClient.cs#13-19) to build it, or just use `PathString`. We will return `$"https://localhost:7192/uploads/images/{fileName}"` for simplicity if CORS works. Since Aspire uses dynamic ports, the best way is to return just the relative path `/uploads/images/filename` and let the Web frontend prepend the `apiservice` BaseAddress when displaying, but since the forms send `ImageUrl`, it's easiest if [ApiClient](file:///c:/Users/Libert/Documents/Visual%20Studio%2018/Projets/GPOE26/GPOE26.Web/Services/ApiClient.cs#13-19) handles constructing the absolute path of the uploaded image if needed. Actually, `ApiService` can generate absolute paths by using the HTTP Request Scheme & Host.

---

### Web Frontend Services

#### [ApiClient.cs](file:///c:/Users/Libert/Documents/Visual%20Studio%2018/Projets/GPOE26/GPOE26.Web/Services/ApiClient.cs)
- Add `UploadImageAsync(Stream file, string fileName)` using the `apiservice` HttpClient. This will hit the new `POST /api/upload` endpoint and return the full URL to the saved image.

---

### Web Frontend UI Components

For each of the following components, we will add an `<InputFile>` component next to the existing `ImageUrl` URL input. We will add an option (radio buttons or a toggle switch, or simply both fields where uploading a file automatically updates the URL input). The simplest approach is providing a standard `InputFile` element that, `OnChange`, immediately uploads the file using `ApiClient.UploadImageAsync` and places the resulting URL directly into the `ImageUrl` text box. 

